1
00:00:41,750 --> 00:00:45,963
THE DREAM LIFE OF MR. KIM

2
00:00:52,469 --> 00:00:54,137
-Honey!
-Hi.

3
00:00:54,638 --> 00:00:55,847
Sorry to keep you waiting.

4
00:01:05,941 --> 00:01:06,900
Excuse me.

5
00:01:09,194 --> 00:01:10,487
Mr. Kim Nak-su?

6
00:01:39,808 --> 00:01:40,851
Should I get a refill?

7
00:01:41,768 --> 00:01:43,770
-No, thanks.
-Okay.

8
00:01:43,854 --> 00:01:46,148
Shall we start talking?

9
00:01:47,566 --> 00:01:48,650
Sure, let's talk.

10
00:01:51,737 --> 00:01:54,072
Which company do you--

11
00:01:54,156 --> 00:01:56,116
You know I work for a credit card company.

12
00:01:56,199 --> 00:01:59,161
Right. A credit card company.

13
00:01:59,244 --> 00:02:01,121
Then what school did you--

14
00:02:01,204 --> 00:02:02,998
Just a junior college.

15
00:02:03,081 --> 00:02:04,207
-Next.
-Next.

16
00:02:05,626 --> 00:02:06,960
Then…

17
00:02:08,462 --> 00:02:11,048
-Par--
-My parents?

18
00:02:11,131 --> 00:02:12,924
No.

19
00:02:13,008 --> 00:02:14,843
Don't you want to know anything about me?

20
00:02:14,926 --> 00:02:16,386
Of course I do.

21
00:02:16,470 --> 00:02:18,347
I really do, but…

22
00:02:20,891 --> 00:02:21,892
I…

23
00:02:23,602 --> 00:02:26,480
I need to use the restroom for a second.

24
00:02:27,439 --> 00:02:28,774
Excuse me.

25
00:02:38,033 --> 00:02:39,910
Damn you, Loafer.
I didn't know that, did I?

26
00:02:41,119 --> 00:02:44,623
I thought I'd be able to talk smoothly,
like I did at job interviews.

27
00:02:44,706 --> 00:02:46,875
Stop with the nagging.
Do you have any tips?

28
00:02:48,502 --> 00:02:49,378
Zodiac sign?

29
00:02:50,003 --> 00:02:51,755
I don't know anything about that stuff.

30
00:03:01,181 --> 00:03:02,516
I HOPE YOU MEET SOMEONE NICE

31
00:03:16,613 --> 00:03:18,907
BUS STOP

32
00:04:04,619 --> 00:04:06,955
First of all, I apologize.

33
00:04:07,038 --> 00:04:08,081
I'm sorry.

34
00:04:08,582 --> 00:04:11,042
It's Sunday today.

35
00:04:11,126 --> 00:04:12,836
The one day we get to rest.

36
00:04:12,919 --> 00:04:14,379
Cut to the chase.

37
00:04:14,463 --> 00:04:15,797
Right.

38
00:04:15,881 --> 00:04:19,843
What good does it do to you
to just leave after an hour?

39
00:04:19,926 --> 00:04:22,554
Considering all the time
and energy you spent preparing for this,

40
00:04:22,637 --> 00:04:24,973
it would be a huge loss for you.

41
00:04:25,056 --> 00:04:25,932
A loss?

42
00:04:26,016 --> 00:04:27,017
Yes.

43
00:04:27,642 --> 00:04:32,147
If I were you, I'd at least treat it
as practice for the next blind date

44
00:04:32,230 --> 00:04:33,607
and sit through it.

45
00:04:33,690 --> 00:04:35,358
Since you came out on the weekend,

46
00:04:35,442 --> 00:04:37,819
you should at least
get something out of it.

47
00:04:39,196 --> 00:04:41,948
We weren't done with the fries,
but you cleared the table.

48
00:04:42,032 --> 00:04:43,450
I finished them.

49
00:04:44,367 --> 00:04:45,744
How greedy of you.

50
00:04:46,286 --> 00:04:47,162
DEBIT CARD RECEIPT

51
00:04:47,245 --> 00:04:49,873
Even college students
have credit cards these days.

52
00:04:49,956 --> 00:04:50,832
How come you don't?

53
00:04:51,541 --> 00:04:52,709
I…

54
00:04:53,460 --> 00:04:55,545
I really am getting a free bike, right?

55
00:04:55,629 --> 00:04:58,215
Jeez, what would I gain from scamming you?

56
00:04:58,298 --> 00:04:59,591
Can I really use

57
00:04:59,674 --> 00:05:02,177
the landline and the internet
at the same time with this?

58
00:05:02,260 --> 00:05:03,136
Of course.

59
00:05:03,220 --> 00:05:04,971
-Do you play Fortress?
-Yes.

60
00:05:05,055 --> 00:05:07,390
You don't have to
go to internet cafes now.

61
00:05:07,474 --> 00:05:09,851
Once you install this,
Fortress runs great at home.

62
00:05:09,935 --> 00:05:11,186
-Really?
-Yes.

63
00:05:12,771 --> 00:05:13,688
I'm done.

64
00:05:14,231 --> 00:05:15,982
-Me too. Thank you.
-Okay.

65
00:05:17,108 --> 00:05:18,985
This month's sales competition is no joke.

66
00:05:19,945 --> 00:05:21,071
I was sweating bullets.

67
00:05:24,115 --> 00:05:26,409
See? Good thing you didn't go home, right?

68
00:05:27,244 --> 00:05:29,287
Well, I did get something out of this.

69
00:05:30,038 --> 00:05:33,124
Why didn't you talk like this before?

70
00:05:35,418 --> 00:05:37,420
It's been a month
since I joined the company,

71
00:05:38,672 --> 00:05:42,217
and this is actually my first time
meeting people outside of work.

72
00:05:42,801 --> 00:05:45,053
My gosh. You must work overtime every day.

73
00:05:45,136 --> 00:05:46,471
Yes.

74
00:05:46,555 --> 00:05:48,723
-Here's your pen.
-Okay.

75
00:06:01,027 --> 00:06:03,154
Do you enjoy your work?

76
00:06:05,615 --> 00:06:07,075
Not really.

77
00:06:07,158 --> 00:06:09,661
Then why not have some fun
instead of overworking yourself?

78
00:06:09,744 --> 00:06:11,496
Otherwise, what's the point of living?

79
00:06:11,580 --> 00:06:12,706
What do you mean?

80
00:06:12,789 --> 00:06:16,626
I need to get promoted, buy a house,
and get married. I should work hard.

81
00:06:17,377 --> 00:06:18,253
When you get married,

82
00:06:19,045 --> 00:06:21,673
are you going to take it easy at work?

83
00:06:29,306 --> 00:06:30,432
You are so beautiful.

84
00:06:32,559 --> 00:06:34,227
Come on now.

85
00:06:35,020 --> 00:06:37,272
Are you trying to get me
to buy something else?

86
00:06:52,537 --> 00:06:54,122
What's so great, Dad?

87
00:06:54,205 --> 00:06:56,374
You survived as a general manager
at a big company,

88
00:06:56,458 --> 00:06:59,210
bought an apartment in Seoul,
and sent me to college. So what?

89
00:07:15,894 --> 00:07:17,270
Where are you going?

90
00:07:21,691 --> 00:07:24,152
I'm going to sleep somewhere else tonight.

91
00:07:24,235 --> 00:07:25,570
Why?

92
00:07:32,410 --> 00:07:34,704
Because I think it's only fair.

93
00:07:36,081 --> 00:07:38,833
I know Dad isn't coming home
because of me.

94
00:07:39,960 --> 00:07:43,213
I'll call him tomorrow and apologize.

95
00:07:44,297 --> 00:07:46,383
I can at least do that much for him.

96
00:07:47,801 --> 00:07:49,844
I won't mean it, though.

97
00:07:52,138 --> 00:07:53,014
Good night.

98
00:07:54,182 --> 00:07:55,350
Su-gyeom.

99
00:07:59,896 --> 00:08:01,231
On your way out,

100
00:08:01,314 --> 00:08:03,650
please throw away the boxes
by the front door.

101
00:08:09,656 --> 00:08:11,366
Is there anything else?

102
00:08:14,744 --> 00:08:15,662
And…

103
00:08:18,957 --> 00:08:21,126
go buy me one more of these, please.

104
00:08:25,463 --> 00:08:26,673
Come on.

105
00:08:36,099 --> 00:08:37,475
Do you know

106
00:08:37,559 --> 00:08:39,644
how I feel

107
00:08:40,478 --> 00:08:42,397
after giving your dad an earful?

108
00:08:44,858 --> 00:08:46,484
It leaves a bad taste in my mouth.

109
00:08:46,568 --> 00:08:50,405
Your dad is absolutely
in the wrong from start to finish.

110
00:08:50,488 --> 00:08:51,656
And yet,

111
00:08:52,323 --> 00:08:54,325
after 10 or 20 minutes,

112
00:08:55,660 --> 00:08:57,787
I'm the one who feels worse.

113
00:08:59,622 --> 00:09:04,210
He always manages to make me apologize,
even when I don't mean it.

114
00:09:05,795 --> 00:09:08,048
"Okay, honey. I'm sorry."

115
00:09:08,548 --> 00:09:10,800
"I think I was wrong."

116
00:09:24,355 --> 00:09:25,732
I'm sorry, son.

117
00:09:26,691 --> 00:09:27,567
I've really

118
00:09:28,818 --> 00:09:30,695
spoiled your dad.

119
00:09:34,199 --> 00:09:35,450
You sure have.

120
00:09:36,284 --> 00:09:37,535
Why did you do that?

121
00:09:41,247 --> 00:09:42,207
I don't know.

122
00:09:44,959 --> 00:09:46,252
I guess

123
00:09:47,378 --> 00:09:51,716
I wanted our home to be the one place
where your father wouldn't feel small.

124
00:09:55,428 --> 00:09:57,972
Also, think about
your dad's face, you know?

125
00:09:58,056 --> 00:10:00,892
When his eyebrows droop like that
and he's all sulky,

126
00:10:02,018 --> 00:10:04,729
he looks so pitiful.

127
00:10:07,732 --> 00:10:09,025
So,

128
00:10:09,109 --> 00:10:12,153
are you giving up on
the real estate license exam too?

129
00:10:23,164 --> 00:10:25,708
I should just mop the floor myself.

130
00:10:25,792 --> 00:10:29,504
What luxury was I hoping for, really?

131
00:10:29,587 --> 00:10:33,091
Goodness, why's this thing
acting up again?

132
00:10:34,467 --> 00:10:36,427
Don't be like me.

133
00:10:37,011 --> 00:10:39,139
You do what you want.

134
00:10:40,265 --> 00:10:42,058
It's okay for children to do that.

135
00:10:42,600 --> 00:10:45,687
You're allowed to do that, Su-gyeom.

136
00:10:52,733 --> 00:10:56,531
EPISODE 3
MVP

137
00:10:56,614 --> 00:10:57,657
I've been using

138
00:10:57,740 --> 00:10:58,992
ACT's fastest

139
00:10:59,075 --> 00:11:02,036
and most expensive Super Giga
Internet Plan for the past two years.

140
00:11:02,120 --> 00:11:02,996
But its actual speed

141
00:11:03,079 --> 00:11:06,416
wasn't even a hundredth
of the speed I'm supposed to get.

142
00:11:06,499 --> 00:11:09,419
I'm sure many other users have experienced

143
00:11:09,502 --> 00:11:11,296
the same issue, not just me.

144
00:11:11,963 --> 00:11:15,133
Until ACT gives a reasonable response,

145
00:11:15,216 --> 00:11:17,135
I'll make sure to get
to the bottom of this.

146
00:11:17,218 --> 00:11:18,219
HEAD OF SALES
HWANG TAE-SAN

147
00:11:18,303 --> 00:11:20,346
This has been your IT-BOY.

148
00:11:20,430 --> 00:11:21,764
IT-BOY WILL GO ALL THE WAY

149
00:11:21,848 --> 00:11:23,183
Turn on the lights.

150
00:11:37,030 --> 00:11:37,947
Is he well-known?

151
00:11:38,031 --> 00:11:40,575
EMERGENCY MEETING ABOUT
YOUTUBER'S EXPOSÉ ON ACT'S INTERNET SPEEDS

152
00:11:40,658 --> 00:11:42,577
-He has over two million subscribers.
-My gosh.

153
00:11:42,660 --> 00:11:44,704
How many articles have been published?

154
00:11:44,787 --> 00:11:46,539
Two online outlets have covered it so far,

155
00:11:46,623 --> 00:11:49,542
but it hasn't hit the main pages
on the web portals yet.

156
00:11:49,626 --> 00:11:52,670
Isn't this an issue
for the Infrastructure Team and not us?

157
00:11:52,754 --> 00:11:54,672
That's true for the YouTuber case,

158
00:11:54,756 --> 00:11:57,342
but our sales division also needs
a full investigation.

159
00:11:57,425 --> 00:11:59,510
If there were any instances
of us proposing contracts

160
00:11:59,594 --> 00:12:01,346
knowing there was no Giga coverage,

161
00:12:01,429 --> 00:12:03,973
we could be sued
for illegal business practices.

162
00:12:06,976 --> 00:12:09,979
The quote was based on Super Giga,
but this area isn't covered yet.

163
00:12:10,063 --> 00:12:11,147
SCHEDULED FOR AUGUST 2025

164
00:12:11,231 --> 00:12:13,524
Get it installed.
It's just a few months at most.

165
00:12:16,444 --> 00:12:18,696
It just made it to the main page.

166
00:12:21,950 --> 00:12:23,409
ACT SLAMMED FOR "FASTEST SPEED" CLAIM

167
00:12:30,375 --> 00:12:33,044
Okay, everyone.

168
00:12:33,127 --> 00:12:36,798
This was supposed to be my day off,
but I came in because of this.

169
00:12:36,881 --> 00:12:38,132
But seeing the state of things,

170
00:12:38,216 --> 00:12:41,761
it doesn't seem like something
that requires my presence.

171
00:12:41,844 --> 00:12:45,890
So, I'd like for you to follow
Mr. Baek's orders

172
00:12:45,974 --> 00:12:48,559
and respond to this issue proactively.

173
00:12:49,185 --> 00:12:51,938
-But, Mr. Hwang--
-Please take a seat.

174
00:12:52,021 --> 00:12:54,774
All right, then. Have a good day.

175
00:13:02,240 --> 00:13:05,368
Who's taking the meeting notes right now?

176
00:13:06,035 --> 00:13:08,204
I am, sir.

177
00:13:08,288 --> 00:13:11,791
I don't think there's any need
to include my name in the attendees list,

178
00:13:11,874 --> 00:13:12,834
don't you think?

179
00:13:12,917 --> 00:13:15,211
I was only here for ten minutes.

180
00:13:16,879 --> 00:13:18,006
Understood, sir.

181
00:13:18,673 --> 00:13:20,216
Have a good day.

182
00:13:29,475 --> 00:13:30,935
Let's take ten.

183
00:13:48,286 --> 00:13:49,162
Mr. Kim.

184
00:13:50,079 --> 00:13:51,205
What is it? Let's talk later.

185
00:13:51,289 --> 00:13:53,041
-I need to go.
-Just one minute, sir.

186
00:13:53,124 --> 00:13:54,375
What is it?

187
00:13:56,336 --> 00:13:59,505
To be honest,
I recorded our conversation that day.

188
00:14:00,048 --> 00:14:00,923
What?

189
00:14:01,007 --> 00:14:03,384
I recorded it when I told you
about the Yangpyeong case.

190
00:14:03,468 --> 00:14:06,888
It is a bit ambiguous,
so I'd like for you to take a look.

191
00:14:09,432 --> 00:14:12,226
You scary bastard.
Why would you record that?

192
00:14:12,310 --> 00:14:14,395
I always do it when I report something.
Just in case.

193
00:14:14,479 --> 00:14:17,273
-I have to watch my back.
-Wow, you're unbelievable.

194
00:14:18,858 --> 00:14:20,818
But that's not what's important.

195
00:14:20,902 --> 00:14:24,072
Before the meeting,
I listened to the recording again,

196
00:14:25,073 --> 00:14:27,575
and Mr. Baek was there
with us at the time, right?

197
00:14:28,326 --> 00:14:29,202
Listen to this.

198
00:14:29,285 --> 00:14:30,244
ACT HEADQUARTERS 10

199
00:14:30,328 --> 00:14:32,705
Yes, but we have to start
the service next week.

200
00:14:32,789 --> 00:14:34,707
What? Is there a problem?

201
00:14:35,375 --> 00:14:37,627
No, sir.

202
00:14:39,379 --> 00:14:41,089
What's there to worry about?

203
00:14:43,925 --> 00:14:45,009
What are you saying?

204
00:14:46,511 --> 00:14:50,264
So, if Mr. Baek decides
to make an issue of this,

205
00:14:50,890 --> 00:14:53,893
shouldn't he also bear
part of the responsibility?

206
00:14:58,856 --> 00:15:01,526
Yes, Mr. Baek. I'll be right there.

207
00:15:05,029 --> 00:15:05,905
Delete that, you punk.

208
00:15:09,700 --> 00:15:11,035
You little…

209
00:15:11,119 --> 00:15:12,662
-Delete it.
-Okay.

210
00:15:12,745 --> 00:15:13,746
-Jeez.
-Okay.

211
00:15:19,585 --> 00:15:20,753
Why would I?

212
00:15:23,965 --> 00:15:24,966
Jeong-tae.

213
00:15:25,883 --> 00:15:27,552
Come on. Lighten up.

214
00:15:28,428 --> 00:15:30,388
You know Hwang Tae-san's
survived three years

215
00:15:30,471 --> 00:15:31,848
just by knowing when to back out.

216
00:15:31,931 --> 00:15:34,434
Gosh, that little weasel.

217
00:15:37,061 --> 00:15:38,980
-Nak-su.
-Yes.

218
00:15:39,063 --> 00:15:40,189
The nails that stick out

219
00:15:40,273 --> 00:15:43,067
get hammered down
during performance review season.

220
00:15:43,151 --> 00:15:46,195
So it's a bit risky for me
to make any big moves right now.

221
00:15:47,280 --> 00:15:50,616
If Hwang Tae-san tells me to crawl,
I have to crawl.

222
00:15:51,159 --> 00:15:53,661
Every time I see him,
he asks me why I played golf

223
00:15:53,744 --> 00:15:56,414
with the directors last time.
It's driving me crazy.

224
00:16:02,837 --> 00:16:03,838
Nak-su.

225
00:16:05,173 --> 00:16:07,925
You don't have anything

226
00:16:09,051 --> 00:16:10,761
they can hold against you, do you?

227
00:16:13,473 --> 00:16:16,100
No, I'm good.

228
00:16:16,184 --> 00:16:17,101
Then…

229
00:16:18,895 --> 00:16:21,272
can you take the lead
and try to sort it out?

230
00:16:22,398 --> 00:16:24,192
Me?

231
00:16:24,275 --> 00:16:27,612
This could actually be
an opportunity for you.

232
00:16:28,696 --> 00:16:29,697
Don't you think so?

233
00:16:30,239 --> 00:16:32,033
Managing Director Kim Nak-su.

234
00:16:37,330 --> 00:16:38,206
You can't do it?

235
00:16:39,665 --> 00:16:42,168
I can. It's a good opportunity.

236
00:16:42,251 --> 00:16:43,127
Understood.

237
00:16:45,421 --> 00:16:46,297
Let's make it work.

238
00:17:12,156 --> 00:17:13,115
Yes.

239
00:17:13,199 --> 00:17:14,075
Goodbye, sir.

240
00:17:14,158 --> 00:17:16,118
Hello.

241
00:17:16,202 --> 00:17:17,078
Hi.

242
00:17:21,874 --> 00:17:23,209
How's that going?

243
00:17:23,834 --> 00:17:24,710
What?

244
00:17:26,629 --> 00:17:27,838
How's what going?

245
00:17:30,299 --> 00:17:31,384
The bomb that dropped today.

246
00:17:31,467 --> 00:17:35,429
I heard some YouTuber totally lost it
over the slow internet speed.

247
00:17:35,513 --> 00:17:37,557
Oh, that one?

248
00:17:38,224 --> 00:17:39,684
It's nothing serious.

249
00:17:39,767 --> 00:17:42,728
It seems pretty serious.
I even saw an article on it online.

250
00:17:44,355 --> 00:17:46,607
No, it's not a big deal.

251
00:17:47,233 --> 00:17:48,651
Our very own…

252
00:17:49,527 --> 00:17:50,611
Nak-su…

253
00:17:51,237 --> 00:17:53,030
will handle it without a problem.

254
00:17:53,114 --> 00:17:53,990
I will.

255
00:17:55,032 --> 00:17:56,409
I see.

256
00:17:56,951 --> 00:17:59,453
After all, you do have
25 years of experience.

257
00:18:00,538 --> 00:18:03,082
Show us what you got.

258
00:18:03,165 --> 00:18:07,128
Show us what you got.
Show us what you got.

259
00:18:09,338 --> 00:18:11,215
I will show you.

260
00:18:11,299 --> 00:18:13,217
I didn't mean to tease you.

261
00:18:17,388 --> 00:18:18,389
Mr. Baek.

262
00:18:23,686 --> 00:18:27,565
Don't you think they're going to try
to pin the blame on the subcontractors?

263
00:18:28,441 --> 00:18:29,900
-Jeez.
-You think so?

264
00:18:30,818 --> 00:18:32,486
That will just make people more upset.

265
00:18:32,570 --> 00:18:35,281
And yet, that's the kind of choice

266
00:18:35,781 --> 00:18:38,326
our company always makes.

267
00:18:56,010 --> 00:18:57,178
I should sit there.

268
00:19:03,184 --> 00:19:05,269
As per Mr. Baek's direction,

269
00:19:05,353 --> 00:19:08,272
I'll be taking charge of this case.

270
00:19:08,356 --> 00:19:11,025
So, let's hear
what everyone thinks, shall we?

271
00:19:11,651 --> 00:19:13,527
-Go on.
-As I mentioned earlier,

272
00:19:13,611 --> 00:19:17,114
the issue is recommending Giga Internet

273
00:19:17,198 --> 00:19:19,283
