463
00:29:14,169 --> 00:29:15,712
Anyway, I believe I can make him

464
00:29:15,796 --> 00:29:18,006
a better offer than what he currently has.

465
00:29:19,299 --> 00:29:20,342
Right.

466
00:29:20,425 --> 00:29:22,177
He's basically saying

467
00:29:22,261 --> 00:29:26,223
he can give Nak-su a bigger salary.

468
00:29:26,306 --> 00:29:27,933
I understand that perfectly.

469
00:29:28,809 --> 00:29:31,186
Can you casually ask him

470
00:29:31,270 --> 00:29:34,398
if he has a plan B
in case there's any issue

471
00:29:34,481 --> 00:29:36,775
with his executive promotion this year?

472
00:29:36,858 --> 00:29:38,735
ACT has a bit of a reputation

473
00:29:38,819 --> 00:29:41,613
for not being flexible in how it operates.

474
00:29:41,697 --> 00:29:45,158
Honestly, I think his talent
is kind of wasted at ACT.

475
00:29:45,242 --> 00:29:46,785
Just look at what happened today.

476
00:29:46,868 --> 00:29:49,788
