522
00:31:45,821 --> 00:31:49,866
I didn't exactly order my team
to make him take it down.

523
00:31:49,950 --> 00:31:52,536
I just floated the idea
that we could try--

524
00:31:54,955 --> 00:31:56,998
What's done is done.

525
00:31:57,082 --> 00:31:59,793
Let's post a corrective order notice
on our website now

526
00:31:59,876 --> 00:32:01,503
and a separate apology statement.

527
00:32:01,586 --> 00:32:03,380
Even if we end up paying a fine,

528
00:32:03,463 --> 00:32:05,841
we need to respond quickly from now on

529
00:32:05,924 --> 00:32:07,592
to minimize the damage to our image.

530
00:32:07,676 --> 00:32:08,718
I agree.

531
00:32:08,802 --> 00:32:11,346
We'll take care of that
on our side right away.

532
00:32:11,430 --> 00:32:14,516
-Okay.
-I need to check something.

533
00:32:14,599 --> 00:32:18,895
Where's the public facility in Yangpyeong
that was mentioned in the recent video?

534
00:32:18,979 --> 00:32:20,689
Who's in charge of that?

535
00:32:23,233 --> 00:32:26,862
You need to be honest about
whether this was intentional or a mistake.

536
00:32:26,945 --> 00:32:28,947
We need to know in order to respond.

537
00:32:29,030 --> 00:32:30,490
If we get an administrative sanction,

538
00:32:30,574 --> 00:32:33,827
worst case, we could have
our business suspended

539
00:32:33,910 --> 00:32:35,579
or even be barred from public bidding.

540
00:32:36,913 --> 00:32:38,748
We'll easily lose tens of billions.

541
00:32:39,499 --> 00:32:42,335
One person's idea
turned into an official company order.

542
00:32:42,419 --> 00:32:44,463
We must investigate
and compensate properly.

543
00:32:44,546 --> 00:32:47,132
Okay. I'll get to the bottom of this.

544
00:32:52,762 --> 00:32:54,723
Do I need to tell you right now?

545
00:32:56,892 --> 00:32:57,767
No.

546
00:32:58,560 --> 00:33:01,146
You can tell us
when you're ready, Mr. Baek.

547
00:33:03,106 --> 00:33:07,819
We'll discuss it
within the sales division first.

548
00:33:24,252 --> 00:33:26,463
-Team 2.
-We were not in charge of this.

549
00:33:27,255 --> 00:33:28,507
You're excused.

550
00:33:32,511 --> 00:33:34,679
-Good work in there, Mr. Do.
-Thanks.

551
00:33:34,763 --> 00:33:36,598
Myung-heon and So-yeon, keep an eye on it.

552
00:33:36,681 --> 00:33:37,849
Yes, sir.

553
00:33:37,933 --> 00:33:39,184
Was it you guys?

554
00:33:40,519 --> 00:33:42,145
Of course it was you guys.

555
00:33:42,229 --> 00:33:43,188
Where is it?

556
00:33:46,441 --> 00:33:48,652
Shall I tell him?

557
00:33:52,239 --> 00:33:54,157
It's Yangpyeong Dream Cultural Center.

558
00:33:55,075 --> 00:33:57,118
The Giga Internet
will be installed in August,

559
00:33:57,202 --> 00:33:59,162
but we signed the contract
without any prior noti--

560
00:33:59,246 --> 00:34:00,914
My gosh.

561
00:34:03,333 --> 00:34:04,209
Kim Nak-su.

562
00:34:05,502 --> 00:34:07,420
What on earth were you thinking?

563
00:34:09,673 --> 00:34:12,634
I'm asking what you were thinking
when you did that!

564
00:34:17,806 --> 00:34:19,015
I apologize.

565
00:34:20,350 --> 00:34:21,393
Leave me with Nak-su.

566
00:34:28,400 --> 00:34:30,652
What the hell were you thinking?

567
00:34:30,735 --> 00:34:33,613
What goes on in that head of yours?
You really--

568
00:34:39,077 --> 00:34:40,662
Let's do what we can.

569
00:34:48,086 --> 00:34:49,045
Nak-su.

570
00:34:49,963 --> 00:34:50,839
Yes.

571
00:34:50,922 --> 00:34:54,551
We've been stuck in this company
for over 20 years.

572
00:34:55,302 --> 00:34:57,137
At this point, it's safe to say

573
00:34:58,263 --> 00:35:00,849
no one here actually likes us.

574
00:35:02,309 --> 00:35:05,645
The higher-ups hate us for not quitting.

575
00:35:05,729 --> 00:35:09,107
Our subordinates hate us
and wonder why we haven't been fired.

576
00:35:09,983 --> 00:35:11,693
You need to know

577
00:35:11,776 --> 00:35:15,030
what you can actually do
from where you stand.

578
00:35:15,113 --> 00:35:18,617
If you can't handle it yourself,
the company won't handle it for you.

579
00:35:18,700 --> 00:35:20,535
They won't wait for you!

580
00:35:23,371 --> 00:35:24,789
Do you feel wronged?

581
00:35:25,498 --> 00:35:26,541
No.

582
00:35:26,625 --> 00:35:29,169
If you can't handle it,
just tell me already.

583
00:35:29,252 --> 00:35:30,462
What's it going to be?

584
00:35:31,880 --> 00:35:34,674
Just say it. If you can't handle it,

585
00:35:34,758 --> 00:35:38,303
I'll tell Do Jin-woo to do it,
whether it's the YouTuber or Yangpyeong.

586
00:35:39,387 --> 00:35:41,556
I'll take care of it, sir.

587
00:35:46,061 --> 00:35:46,978
Nak-su.

588
00:35:48,104 --> 00:35:49,022
Yes.

589
00:35:54,694 --> 00:35:56,446
You really are running out of time.

590
00:35:57,072 --> 00:35:58,365
You have to change.

591
00:35:59,449 --> 00:36:01,576
You have to take responsibility

592
00:36:02,744 --> 00:36:04,663
for all the choices you made.

593
00:36:19,219 --> 00:36:20,095
Okay.

594
00:36:26,309 --> 00:36:27,477
Yes.

595
00:36:27,560 --> 00:36:29,813
I'll connect you
to the Technical Support Team right away.

596
00:36:29,896 --> 00:36:31,314
SCAMMED BY ACT FOR TWO YEARS

597
00:36:31,398 --> 00:36:32,732
Wow. Over three million views.

598
00:36:32,816 --> 00:36:33,942
3.01 MILLION VIEWS

599
00:36:35,527 --> 00:36:37,946
Are you actually laughing now?

600
00:36:38,738 --> 00:36:41,449
A person with real class laughs
through the hard times.

601
00:36:44,411 --> 00:36:45,704
The Yangpyeong case…

602
00:36:45,787 --> 00:36:48,832
If what the Legal Team said is true,
this is a major incident.

603
00:36:48,915 --> 00:36:51,000
I won't get dragged into it, will I?

604
00:36:53,336 --> 00:36:54,337
Here he comes.

605
00:37:02,554 --> 00:37:04,264
For you, sir.

606
00:37:11,813 --> 00:37:13,398
-Ik-hyeon.
-Yes, sir.

607
00:37:13,481 --> 00:37:14,858
Let's step outside for a moment.

608
00:37:16,901 --> 00:37:17,902
Shall I join you?

609
00:37:40,133 --> 00:37:41,009
Mr. Kim,

610
00:37:42,051 --> 00:37:43,720
let's work with Team 2 for now.

611
00:37:45,638 --> 00:37:49,642
We don't have time to deal with both
the YouTuber and Yangpyeong right now.

612
00:37:49,726 --> 00:37:51,478
Let Team 2 handle the YouTuber,

613
00:37:51,561 --> 00:37:53,897
and we'll head to Yangpyeong right now

614
00:37:54,397 --> 00:37:55,857
and beg for forgiveness.

615
00:37:56,941 --> 00:37:59,319
We'll tell them

616
00:37:59,402 --> 00:38:01,571
we'll waive next year's fees.

617
00:38:02,572 --> 00:38:05,909
I'll talk to the Customer Support Team.
They'll make it happen.

618
00:38:09,245 --> 00:38:13,124
If you feel uncomfortable asking
Do Jin-woo about the YouTuber, I'll do it.

619
00:38:14,125 --> 00:38:17,253
It's not that I feel uncomfortable
about it.

620
00:38:18,421 --> 00:38:20,590
Can't we handle the YouTuber case

621
00:38:21,257 --> 00:38:23,134
and let Do handle the Yangpyeong case?

622
00:38:23,927 --> 00:38:24,844
Why?

623
00:38:24,928 --> 00:38:26,679
What do you mean, why?

624
00:38:26,763 --> 00:38:28,681
The Yangpyeong case
is clearly our responsibility.

625
00:38:28,765 --> 00:38:31,017
Why would we make Team 2 clean it up?

626
00:38:31,100 --> 00:38:33,144
Do Jin-woo's close with the Tech Team.

627
00:38:33,228 --> 00:38:34,604
I even saw him earlier

628
00:38:34,687 --> 00:38:36,397
-talking with Jun-seop--
-We can't do that.

629
00:38:37,440 --> 00:38:38,399
Right?

630
00:38:38,483 --> 00:38:40,235
-I guess we can't.
-No, sir.

631
00:38:42,403 --> 00:38:44,280
You really think so?

632
00:38:45,615 --> 00:38:47,200
Do Jin-woo might actually prefer that.

633
00:38:47,283 --> 00:38:48,159
Even if…

634
00:38:48,785 --> 00:38:50,245
even if that were the case,

635
00:38:50,912 --> 00:38:52,956
we need to clean up our own mess.

636
00:38:54,332 --> 00:38:55,834
-Right?
-It's the right thing to do.

637
00:38:55,917 --> 00:38:57,502
Yes, I know.

638
00:38:58,461 --> 00:39:00,380
But…

639
00:39:01,881 --> 00:39:04,592
All eyes in the company
are on us right now.

640
00:39:05,218 --> 00:39:08,304
The Yangpyeong incident
is just a minor mix-up with the client.

641
00:39:08,388 --> 00:39:10,223
Right now,
whoever fixes this YouTuber mess

642
00:39:10,306 --> 00:39:12,183
becomes the MVP.

643
00:39:12,267 --> 00:39:14,394
Ik-hyeon, you don't understand.

644
00:39:14,477 --> 00:39:18,565
I can't afford to take it slow
and go step by step right now.

645
00:39:18,648 --> 00:39:21,609
I need to show off tangible results.
That's the position I'm in.

646
00:39:22,360 --> 00:39:24,195
You don't know the half of it.

647
00:39:26,155 --> 00:39:27,031
What?

648
00:39:27,782 --> 00:39:28,867
What is it?

649
00:39:30,201 --> 00:39:32,287
Come on. You know this is how I am.

650
00:39:32,370 --> 00:39:34,414
You've known me for over a decade.
You know me.

651
00:39:34,497 --> 00:39:35,874
-You--
-Mr. Kim.

652
00:39:39,794 --> 00:39:41,462
Fine. Don't look at me like that.

653
00:39:41,546 --> 00:39:43,423
Okay. Let's go.

654
00:39:44,424 --> 00:39:45,508
You think

655
00:39:46,342 --> 00:39:48,094
we shouldn't handle
the YouTuber case, right?

656
00:39:48,177 --> 00:39:49,220
We shouldn't.

657
00:39:49,971 --> 00:39:51,598
-Are you sure?
-Definitely.

658
00:39:52,265 --> 00:39:54,434
-Wouldn't Jin-woo prefer that?
-We can't, sir.

659
00:41:11,302 --> 00:41:12,679
The weather's really nice.

660
00:41:19,102 --> 00:41:20,812
Have you sorted out your thoughts?

661
00:41:26,484 --> 00:41:28,361
I'm sorry. I'm getting more confused.

662
00:41:29,696 --> 00:41:30,738
Still?

663
00:41:32,407 --> 00:41:34,742
I don't want to live like my dad.

664
00:41:34,826 --> 00:41:36,577
That's for sure.

665
00:41:39,205 --> 00:41:42,000
Do you honestly think
I'm a good fit for this company?

666
00:41:44,252 --> 00:41:45,128
You're not.

667
00:41:47,714 --> 00:41:49,340
Then why did you recommend me?

668
00:41:50,591 --> 00:41:52,343
Do you remember back in middle school?

669
00:41:54,470 --> 00:41:55,471
Middle school?

670
00:41:56,347 --> 00:41:58,307
Back in eighth grade,

671
00:41:58,808 --> 00:42:00,893
they took my earrings
during a random bag search.

672
00:42:02,603 --> 00:42:04,105
You were the class president.

673
00:42:04,188 --> 00:42:06,733
After it was over,
you went to the teacher's office and said,

674
00:42:06,816 --> 00:42:10,737
"Han-na wasn't wearing them.
She just had them in her bag."

675
00:42:10,820 --> 00:42:13,990
"Confiscating them seems a bit harsh."

676
00:42:14,657 --> 00:42:16,284
And you got them back for me.

677
00:42:16,367 --> 00:42:17,243
I did?

678
00:42:18,911 --> 00:42:22,874
Do you remember what you said to me
as you were handing me back my earrings?

679
00:42:23,833 --> 00:42:26,711
You told me not to bring
stuff like that to school,

680
00:42:27,336 --> 00:42:30,590
saying it would be my loss
if I got a bad school record.

681
00:42:30,673 --> 00:42:32,842
That's the Kim Su-gyeom I remember.

682
00:42:34,093 --> 00:42:36,054
A kid with a peculiar rebellious streak

683
00:42:36,804 --> 00:42:38,848
and a stubborn, by-the-book nature.

684
00:42:44,687 --> 00:42:46,272
I knew it. I don't belong here.

685
00:42:47,607 --> 00:42:49,567
I recommended you because you don't.

686
00:42:50,193 --> 00:42:54,280
Your by-the-book nature
could help keep us grounded.

687
00:42:56,115 --> 00:42:59,494
Thanks to you, I ended up
with a clean school record back then.

688
00:43:09,587 --> 00:43:11,881
We'll go to Yangpyeong
and handle it ourselves.

689
00:43:11,964 --> 00:43:15,760
As for the YouTuber case, I think
it's better to explain face-to-face.

690
00:43:15,843 --> 00:43:17,804
I already asked the Tech Team for support.

691
00:43:17,887 --> 00:43:20,515
I've prepared all the tech materials,

692
00:43:20,598 --> 00:43:22,725
and we'll tidy it up
with the PR Team later.

693
00:43:22,809 --> 00:43:25,353
-Mr. Kim, I have the car ready.
-Sure. Let's do that.

694
00:43:25,436 --> 00:43:27,647
If you're ready,
we can head to Yangpyeong now.

695
00:43:27,730 --> 00:43:28,815
Okay.

696
00:43:31,776 --> 00:43:32,902
Song-hee.

697
00:43:32,985 --> 00:43:35,446
What are you doing?
You're coming with us, right?

698
00:43:36,739 --> 00:43:37,657
Me?

699
00:43:41,160 --> 00:43:43,246
-Of course, I should.
-Okay.

700
00:43:43,329 --> 00:43:46,833
It's better if several of us
apologize together.

701
00:43:47,625 --> 00:43:48,709
Okay.

702
00:43:50,044 --> 00:43:53,089
Once we're done, I know a restaurant
that does great griddle jjajang.

703
00:43:53,172 --> 00:43:54,632
It'll be my treat.

704
00:43:54,715 --> 00:43:57,051
That sounds delicious.

705
00:43:59,428 --> 00:44:02,473
We'll be heading out first, Mr. Kim.

706
00:44:02,557 --> 00:44:04,225
Okay.

707
00:44:04,308 --> 00:44:07,145
I'll bring Jun-seop
and a member of the Tech Team with me.

708
00:44:07,228 --> 00:44:08,729
We'll keep you posted.

709
00:44:10,189 --> 00:44:11,774
Are you going to the YouTuber's house?

710
00:44:11,858 --> 00:44:14,402
No, we're meeting
his agency's CEO first for now.

711
00:44:14,485 --> 00:44:17,613
The YouTuber seems reluctant
to meet us himself.

712
00:44:18,614 --> 00:44:20,449
Okay. Good luck.

713
00:44:20,533 --> 00:44:22,493
I'll make sure to take care of it.

714
00:44:25,371 --> 00:44:26,622
Thank you.

715
00:44:28,708 --> 00:44:30,001
-Mr. Kim.
-Yes.

716
00:44:30,084 --> 00:44:33,045
There's heavy traffic, so it'll take
about an hour and 40 minutes.

717
00:44:33,129 --> 00:44:35,256
-We should hurry.
-Okay. Jeez.

718
00:44:35,339 --> 00:44:37,133
Let's go, Song-hee.

719
00:44:37,216 --> 00:44:38,593
Okay.

720
00:44:40,219 --> 00:44:41,220
Hello.

721
00:44:41,304 --> 00:44:42,388
Hello, it's me.

722
00:44:43,598 --> 00:44:44,932
Who…

723
00:44:45,558 --> 00:44:46,559
It's me, Sang-cheol.

724
00:44:46,642 --> 00:44:48,561
Don't you have my number saved?

725
00:44:48,644 --> 00:44:49,812
Sang-cheol…

726
00:44:49,896 --> 00:44:51,689
Oh, hi! What's going on?

727
00:44:53,816 --> 00:44:54,692
What?

728
00:44:58,863 --> 00:45:00,281
Hang on.

729
00:45:00,364 --> 00:45:02,200
Give me a second.

730
00:45:02,283 --> 00:45:05,244
-What? Yes.
-The YouTuber, the IT-BOY.

731
00:45:05,328 --> 00:45:06,662
He's an acquaintance of mine.

732
00:45:06,746 --> 00:45:07,788
Really?

733
00:45:07,872 --> 00:45:10,583
Yes, we've had drinks
together a few times.

734
00:45:10,666 --> 00:45:14,295
If it's all right with you, I'll organize
a meeting and arrange a time.

735
00:45:14,378 --> 00:45:16,505
Really? Can we do that today?

736
00:45:16,589 --> 00:45:19,217
Of course! He's my friend's best friend.

737
00:45:19,717 --> 00:45:21,344
Is that so?

738
00:45:21,427 --> 00:45:22,303
Yes.

739
00:45:22,386 --> 00:45:25,556
Honestly, this shouldn't have
escalated this far.

740
00:45:25,640 --> 00:45:28,392
I got frustrated just seeing
how things were unfolding.

741
00:45:28,476 --> 00:45:30,645
Tell me about it.

742
00:45:31,187 --> 00:45:34,190
That's why I contacted you.

743
00:45:34,273 --> 00:45:37,276
I thought maybe I could be
of some help to you.

744
00:45:39,946 --> 00:45:42,949
By the way, who was it?

745
00:45:43,032 --> 00:45:44,784
What kind of idiot

746
00:45:44,867 --> 00:45:47,161
tells a YouTuber to take their video down?

747
00:45:47,245 --> 00:45:50,081
Just some idiot. A totally crazy idiot.

748
00:45:50,164 --> 00:45:52,208
Okay. Give me a minute.

749
00:45:52,291 --> 00:45:54,502
I'll get back to you right away.

750
00:46:00,174 --> 00:46:01,259
Thank you.

751
00:46:01,342 --> 00:46:03,678
Have some of this. Have some coffee.

752
00:46:06,806 --> 00:46:08,432
-Where did Jin-woo go?
-Sorry?

753
00:46:08,516 --> 00:46:09,725
Jin-woo.

754
00:46:09,809 --> 00:46:11,185
Which way did he go?

755
00:46:11,269 --> 00:46:12,687
-This way or that way?
-Over there.

756
00:46:12,770 --> 00:46:14,021
-There.
-This way?

757
00:46:14,105 --> 00:46:16,148
Where are you going, Mr. Kim?

758
00:46:17,108 --> 00:46:19,360
What's his deal now?

759
00:46:50,558 --> 00:46:51,600
Jin-woo!

760
00:46:53,436 --> 00:46:54,353
Wait!

761
00:46:56,564 --> 00:46:58,816
What's going on, Mr. Kim?

762
00:46:59,650 --> 00:47:00,526
I don't think

763
00:47:01,027 --> 00:47:03,237
we need to contact the agency.

764
00:47:03,904 --> 00:47:05,239
What do you mean?

765
00:47:05,323 --> 00:47:08,826
I've got a direct line to the YouTuber.

766
00:47:08,909 --> 00:47:12,204
I think I can meet him
one-on-one and sort this out.

767
00:47:12,288 --> 00:47:13,998
Great. If you give me his contact,

768
00:47:14,081 --> 00:47:16,000
-I'll reach out and handle--
-No.

769
00:47:16,083 --> 00:47:18,502
You don't need to trouble
yourself with that.

770
00:47:18,586 --> 00:47:20,755
My team will handle this matter. Okay?

771
00:47:20,838 --> 00:47:21,839
But we should--

772
00:47:21,922 --> 00:47:24,467
No, I feel bad as it is.
I know how busy you are.

773
00:47:24,550 --> 00:47:26,761
You really don't need
to concern yourself with this.

774
00:47:26,844 --> 00:47:27,762
We'll handle it.

775
00:47:27,845 --> 00:47:31,140
Since he's a tech YouTuber,

776
00:47:31,223 --> 00:47:33,184
the Tech Team should join
to explain the details.

777
00:47:33,267 --> 00:47:36,771
You can sum it up in a document
and give it to us.

778
00:47:36,854 --> 00:47:37,980
That will do.

779
00:47:38,064 --> 00:47:41,525
What's that? Is that the document?
Give it to me.

780
00:47:41,609 --> 00:47:43,861
Let me have that.

781
00:47:44,570 --> 00:47:46,864
I can read it
and explain it to him, right?

782
00:47:47,531 --> 00:47:49,575
Your resources are too valuable
to waste on this.

783
00:47:49,658 --> 00:47:51,702
Go rest up. What's that? A gift?

784
00:47:52,453 --> 00:47:53,621
Give me that.

785
00:47:54,663 --> 00:47:57,625
Head back in. We'll handle this.

786
00:47:58,250 --> 00:47:59,543
See you.

787
00:48:00,836 --> 00:48:02,630
Sorry?

788
00:48:02,713 --> 00:48:04,673
Mr. Kim? Hello?

789
00:48:05,299 --> 00:48:06,425
Was that Mr. Kim?

790
00:48:06,509 --> 00:48:08,052
-Yes.
-What did he say?

791
00:48:09,970 --> 00:48:13,265
He said to go on head
to Yangpyeong by ourselves.

792
00:48:15,101 --> 00:48:17,186
-What the…
-I'll be monitoring it

793
00:48:17,269 --> 00:48:18,604
-in real time.
-Ik-hyeon.

794
00:48:19,313 --> 00:48:20,272
You got the news, right?

795
00:48:20,356 --> 00:48:22,024
What is going on?

796
00:48:22,108 --> 00:48:24,235
Mr. Kim said he'll meet the YouTuber
and resolve this.

797
00:48:24,318 --> 00:48:25,694
It's better this way.

798
00:48:26,320 --> 00:48:27,446
I'm sorry.

799
00:48:27,530 --> 00:48:29,115
Please. You didn't do anything wrong.

800
00:48:30,157 --> 00:48:31,784
Keep up the good work.

801
00:48:31,867 --> 00:48:32,743
Good luck.

802
00:48:32,827 --> 00:48:34,787
Thank you.

803
00:48:40,459 --> 00:48:43,671
-I'm sorry.
-It's fine. I got it.

804
00:48:48,509 --> 00:48:50,302
Yes, I talked to him.

805
00:48:50,386 --> 00:48:52,805
I'll text you the address.
We'll meet you there.

806
00:48:52,888 --> 00:48:54,515
Don't worry about it.

807
00:48:55,182 --> 00:48:56,308
Take your time.

808
00:48:56,809 --> 00:48:58,894
Thank you so much.

809
00:48:58,978 --> 00:49:00,354
Please. No need to worry now.

810
00:49:00,438 --> 00:49:02,189
You came through big-time.

811
00:49:02,273 --> 00:49:04,191
I'll see you at home, Ha-yeong.

812
00:49:04,275 --> 00:49:05,776
-See you.
-Okay.

813
00:49:05,860 --> 00:49:06,819
Bye, Ha-jin.

814
00:49:06,902 --> 00:49:08,028
-Bye.
-I'll get going then.

815
00:49:08,112 --> 00:49:09,488
-Thank you.
-See you.

816
00:49:09,572 --> 00:49:10,614
-Bye.
-Goodbye.

817
00:49:12,908 --> 00:49:15,995
You really have
the best sister in the world.

818
00:49:16,078 --> 00:49:19,874
It would be great if your husband
could start working with Sang-cheol.

819
00:49:19,957 --> 00:49:23,294
In times like these,
family should stick together.

820
00:49:23,377 --> 00:49:26,172
That wasn't free lunch today.
I've given you a mission.

821
00:49:27,339 --> 00:49:30,593
I was so distracted earlier
that I didn't quite catch it.

822
00:49:30,676 --> 00:49:32,553
So what is it that Sang-cheol does?

823
00:49:34,638 --> 00:49:37,933
See? Even if we tell you,
you don't get it.

824
00:49:38,767 --> 00:49:40,519
It's fintech.

825
00:49:40,603 --> 00:49:43,230
Then elaborate on what it is for me

826
00:49:43,314 --> 00:49:45,149
and stop treating me like a fool.

827
00:49:50,321 --> 00:49:51,530
It's like…

828
00:49:52,156 --> 00:49:53,949
It's fintech.

829
00:49:55,075 --> 00:49:57,912
So what the heck is that? Jeez!

830
00:49:58,454 --> 00:49:59,622
He's so…

831
00:49:59,705 --> 00:50:02,124
He's super annoying.

832
00:50:02,708 --> 00:50:03,792
Shall we play some music?

833
00:50:03,876 --> 00:50:04,752
Good idea.

834
00:50:06,253 --> 00:50:08,631
How can a person be this annoying?

835
00:50:08,714 --> 00:50:11,050
You think he's like this at home?
His wife must go crazy.

836
00:50:11,133 --> 00:50:13,969
Just listen to the music.

837
00:50:14,053 --> 00:50:15,763
Focus on the rhythm and the tempo.

838
00:50:15,846 --> 00:50:18,891
Let's pick up some refreshments
for the staff on our way there.

839
00:50:18,974 --> 00:50:20,392
We can't go empty-handed.

840
00:50:20,476 --> 00:50:21,477
Good idea.

841
00:50:21,560 --> 00:50:23,187
Am I the only one who's annoyed?

842
00:50:23,270 --> 00:50:25,356
-Hello?
-I'm always the only one who's annoyed!

843
00:50:26,815 --> 00:50:28,859
-Hello, Nak-su.
-Hello.

844
00:50:28,943 --> 00:50:30,569
-How long has it been?
-How are you?

845
00:50:30,653 --> 00:50:31,862
-Here.
-For me?

846
00:50:33,405 --> 00:50:35,324
This is the friend I told you about.

847
00:50:35,407 --> 00:50:36,867
-Nice to meet you.
-Likewise.

848
00:50:36,951 --> 00:50:38,911
I'm Kim Nak-su from ACT Sales Team 1.

849
00:50:38,994 --> 00:50:40,120
It's nothing big, but…

850
00:50:40,663 --> 00:50:42,957
I won't ever forget the favor
you did for me.

851
00:50:43,040 --> 00:50:44,500
Oh, please.

852
00:50:44,583 --> 00:50:47,419
It'll be nice to see IT-BOY after so long.

853
00:50:47,503 --> 00:50:49,880
How is he? Has he calmed down a bit?

854
00:50:49,964 --> 00:50:51,590
I've buttered him up a bit.

855
00:50:51,674 --> 00:50:54,635
From what I saw,
it seemed like a simple technical issue.

856
00:50:54,718 --> 00:50:57,721
Exactly. It's just a simple issue.

857
00:50:57,805 --> 00:51:00,975
This would have been prevented
with better communication.

858
00:51:01,058 --> 00:51:02,601
-Exactly.
-Exactly.

859
00:51:02,685 --> 00:51:05,437
I'll explain everything
and clear up any misunderstandings.

860
00:51:05,521 --> 00:51:07,565
-Okay. Let's go.
-Thank you so much.

861
00:51:07,648 --> 00:51:08,899
-Let's go.
-Thank you.

862
00:51:09,483 --> 00:51:12,278
-How are things at ACT these days?
-We're barely scraping by.

863
00:51:12,361 --> 00:51:14,738
Come on. I know how competent you are.

864
00:51:14,822 --> 00:51:16,657
-Let me take that.
-It's fine. Let me.

865
00:51:16,740 --> 00:51:17,658
-I can…
-This way.

866
00:51:19,910 --> 00:51:22,621
This is Mr. Kim Nak-su,
a general manager at ACT.

867
00:51:26,792 --> 00:51:27,668
This is for you.

868
00:51:27,751 --> 00:51:30,421
-Goodness.
-You shouldn't have.

869
00:51:31,839 --> 00:51:33,048
I feel bad.

870
00:51:33,591 --> 00:51:36,510
The red areas indicate
completed Giga network construction,

871
00:51:36,594 --> 00:51:40,264
and the blue areas indicate
planned construction, as you can see.

872
00:51:40,347 --> 00:51:41,974
But if you look here…

873
00:51:42,057 --> 00:51:44,101
I can't believe a major Korean corporation

874
00:51:44,184 --> 00:51:47,730
would stoop so low to cheat
a small public facility!

875
00:51:48,355 --> 00:51:49,732
-We are very sorry.
-We apologize

876
00:51:49,815 --> 00:51:51,609
-We're sorry.
-Hold on.

877
00:51:51,692 --> 00:51:53,360
The person in charge didn't come?

878
00:51:55,279 --> 00:51:56,572
Regardless of the reason,

879
00:51:56,655 --> 00:51:58,282
I once again express my deepest apologies.

880
00:51:58,365 --> 00:52:00,200
Okay.

881
00:52:00,284 --> 00:52:01,702
-All right.
-I mean it.

882
00:52:01,785 --> 00:52:02,953
Anyway,

883
00:52:03,037 --> 00:52:06,206
we're truly grateful to you, IT-BOY.

884
00:52:06,290 --> 00:52:09,752
You bringing this issue to light
keeps us on our toes

885
00:52:09,835 --> 00:52:12,129
and pushes us to make our service better--

886
00:52:12,796 --> 00:52:14,089
-Gosh.
-Let me.

887
00:52:14,173 --> 00:52:15,841
-Let me.
-No, please. Here.

888
00:52:16,425 --> 00:52:17,718
Here.

889
00:52:18,552 --> 00:52:20,346
The person in charge should've come!

890
00:52:20,429 --> 00:52:22,014
What are you all doing here?

891
00:52:22,097 --> 00:52:23,349
Is this some joke?

892
00:52:23,432 --> 00:52:24,516
We're sorry.

893
00:52:24,600 --> 00:52:25,726
-We're sorry.
-We're sorry.

894
00:52:25,809 --> 00:52:28,437
By the way, whose idea was it
to have me take down the video?

895
00:52:28,520 --> 00:52:30,105
It caught me off guard

896
00:52:30,189 --> 00:52:32,650
when I was told
to take the video down out of nowhere.

897
00:52:32,733 --> 00:52:36,403
The bastard who was dumb enough
to ask you to take it down…

898
00:52:37,112 --> 00:52:38,906
I mean, the employee…

899
00:52:38,989 --> 00:52:41,992
I will take responsibility
and ensure that the employee

900
00:52:42,076 --> 00:52:44,078
faces appropriate disciplinary action.

901
00:52:44,787 --> 00:52:45,788
I'm sorry.

902
00:52:45,871 --> 00:52:47,498
We'll make the service free for a year

903
00:52:47,581 --> 00:52:49,124
as a token of our apology--

904
00:52:49,208 --> 00:52:51,627
I don't need that.
Just hand me the contract.

905
00:52:51,710 --> 00:52:53,003
Here.

906
00:52:54,171 --> 00:52:56,715
-I'm so sorry.
-Goodness.

907
00:52:56,799 --> 00:52:58,967
Can we…

908
00:53:11,980 --> 00:53:13,232
What are you still doing here?

909
00:53:13,315 --> 00:53:14,900
We're very sorry.

910
00:53:14,983 --> 00:53:16,193
Go!

911
00:53:16,276 --> 00:53:18,821
-We're sorry.
-We're sorry.

912
00:53:36,797 --> 00:53:39,299
Call Mr. Baek Jeong-tae.

913
00:53:39,383 --> 00:53:41,009
Okay. Calling.

914
00:53:42,928 --> 00:53:43,971
Hello, Nak-su.

915
00:53:44,054 --> 00:53:47,099
Sir, it's all taken care of.

916
00:53:47,182 --> 00:53:48,350
Okay. Well done.

917
00:53:48,434 --> 00:53:51,061
I gave a proper apology

918
00:53:51,145 --> 00:53:54,898
and explained
the technical issues in detail.

919
00:53:54,982 --> 00:53:57,860
He agreed to upload
a follow-up video right away,

920
00:53:57,943 --> 00:53:59,820
and I've handled everything.

921
00:53:59,903 --> 00:54:01,905
It all went well.

922
00:54:01,989 --> 00:54:05,492
-How about Yangpyeong?
-As for Yangpyeong…

923
00:54:06,118 --> 00:54:09,121
It went well in Yangpyeong too.

924
00:54:09,204 --> 00:54:10,122
It did?

925
00:54:10,205 --> 00:54:13,959
I made sure my team knew what to do.

926
00:54:14,042 --> 00:54:15,127
Okay.

927
00:54:15,210 --> 00:54:17,504
Are you at the office?

928
00:54:18,255 --> 00:54:20,174
I'm almost there.

929
00:54:20,257 --> 00:54:22,968
If you haven't eaten,
shall we grab dinner?

930
00:54:23,051 --> 00:54:23,969
No.

931
00:54:24,052 --> 00:54:25,929
I'm actually with someone now.

932
00:54:26,472 --> 00:54:29,016
Are you? Okay.

933
00:54:29,516 --> 00:54:30,976
Good job today.

934
00:54:31,059 --> 00:54:32,436
-Jeong-tae!
-What?

935
00:54:33,312 --> 00:54:35,481
I'm sorry. I'll do better.

936
00:54:36,023 --> 00:54:37,149
Okay.

937
00:54:37,232 --> 00:54:39,151
-I'll do better!
-Okay.

938
00:54:39,234 --> 00:54:40,152
I--

939
00:54:47,493 --> 00:54:50,454
What's the point
of nagging him over and over

940
00:54:50,537 --> 00:54:52,331
when he just doesn't get it?

941
00:54:56,543 --> 00:54:58,420
He's still stuck with the mindset

942
00:54:58,504 --> 00:55:01,673
of a student waiting
for his homework to be checked.

943
00:55:01,757 --> 00:55:04,384
I'm seriously fuming.

944
00:55:05,636 --> 00:55:06,720
Let me.

945
00:55:13,769 --> 00:55:16,146
Should we order some more tuna belly?

946
00:55:16,230 --> 00:55:17,147
Sounds good.

947
00:55:17,773 --> 00:55:19,149
Ms. Woo.

948
00:55:20,317 --> 00:55:21,944
I'm just glad things worked out well.

949
00:55:24,404 --> 00:55:25,823
Where were we?

950
00:55:27,157 --> 00:55:30,118
MVP.

951
00:55:30,786 --> 00:55:31,745
Right.

952
00:55:31,829 --> 00:55:33,247
SONG IK-HYEON

953
00:55:33,330 --> 00:55:35,415
-Hello, Ik-hyeon.
-Mr. Kim.

954
00:55:35,499 --> 00:55:37,376
We're just leaving Yangpyeong now.

955
00:55:37,459 --> 00:55:38,877
Okay. How did everything go?

956
00:55:39,753 --> 00:55:41,338
It's been taken care of for now.

957
00:55:41,421 --> 00:55:43,382
I don't think they'll take it to court.

958
00:55:43,465 --> 00:55:45,217
What a relief.

959
00:55:45,300 --> 00:55:47,427
It went well with the YouTuber too.

960
00:55:47,511 --> 00:55:48,762
I told you.

961
00:55:48,846 --> 00:55:51,598
People who live off ads and sponsorships
will always fold.

962
00:55:51,682 --> 00:55:54,059
I showed up, frowned, and pointed out

963
00:55:54,142 --> 00:55:56,562
that it clearly says
"construction planned."

964
00:55:56,645 --> 00:55:58,981
He panicked
and said he'd delete the video,

965
00:55:59,064 --> 00:55:59,982
then apologized.

966
00:56:01,108 --> 00:56:02,734
You should have seen it.

967
00:56:03,652 --> 00:56:04,528
Well done, sir.

968
00:56:04,611 --> 00:56:08,156
What did they say when you told them
we'd waive their fees?

969
00:56:10,075 --> 00:56:11,952
They declined and asked
to cancel the contract,

970
00:56:12,035 --> 00:56:13,954
so we canceled it
without the termination fee.

971
00:56:14,037 --> 00:56:15,622
I see.

972
00:56:15,706 --> 00:56:17,499
That was the best we could do.

973
00:56:18,208 --> 00:56:19,293
Okay.

974
00:56:19,793 --> 00:56:20,752
I'm sorry about today.

975
00:56:22,629 --> 00:56:23,505
Don't worry about it.

976
00:56:23,589 --> 00:56:26,633
It's not like they were
a major client or anything.

977
00:56:26,717 --> 00:56:27,759
You know?

978
00:56:27,843 --> 00:56:30,846
Let's just work hard
and find us more clients, okay?

979
00:56:30,929 --> 00:56:32,931
Okay. Have a good night, sir.

980
00:56:33,015 --> 00:56:36,351
You guys must be hungry.
Let's have dinner.

981
00:56:37,102 --> 00:56:37,978
Dinner?

982
00:56:38,061 --> 00:56:40,564
You've done so well today.

983
00:56:41,148 --> 00:56:42,441
We should have a company dinner.

984
00:56:42,524 --> 00:56:44,192
Everyone's coming, right?

985
00:56:44,276 --> 00:56:46,069
Yes, but…

986
00:56:46,153 --> 00:56:47,696
Let's go to Ttokdari Diner.

987
00:56:47,779 --> 00:56:50,282
Days like this call for a drink.

988
00:56:50,365 --> 00:56:52,326
Let me ask them first.

989
00:56:52,409 --> 00:56:54,328
What do you mean? Aren't you on speaker?

990
00:56:54,411 --> 00:56:56,246
Come if you're free.

991
00:56:56,330 --> 00:56:58,749
I'm almost there. I'll order first.

992
00:56:58,832 --> 00:56:59,917
Pork neck for you, Song-hee.

993
00:57:00,000 --> 00:57:01,001
That's right!

994
00:57:01,084 --> 00:57:03,211
We'll call you back, Mr. Kim.

995
00:57:03,295 --> 00:57:05,005
No need to do that!

996
00:57:05,088 --> 00:57:07,507
Just come if you're free.
Don't force yourself if you're tired.

997
00:57:07,591 --> 00:57:09,051
I'll see you all soon.

998
00:57:09,134 --> 00:57:10,302
Mr. Kim.

999
00:57:12,304 --> 00:57:14,973
Great.

1000
00:57:15,057 --> 00:57:16,808
Do you two

1001
00:57:17,309 --> 00:57:18,352
have plans tonight?

1002
00:57:20,354 --> 00:57:22,230
Dinner with my boyfriend.

1003
00:57:22,731 --> 00:57:24,608
I made a reservation a month ago.

1004
00:57:25,359 --> 00:57:28,278
It's on a whole different level
from Ttokdari Diner.

1005
00:57:29,071 --> 00:57:30,530
And you, Sung-gu?

1006
00:57:30,614 --> 00:57:33,033
The fifth round of the wedding dress hunt.

1007
00:57:33,617 --> 00:57:35,035
The fifth round?

1008
00:57:35,619 --> 00:57:38,246
Are there even
any dresses left for her to try on?

1009
00:57:38,330 --> 00:57:39,748
What do you say?

1010
00:57:45,170 --> 00:57:46,421
I'll set course for Ttokdari.

1011
00:57:46,505 --> 00:57:48,006
Why is there no end to my work?

1012
00:57:48,090 --> 00:57:49,591
-Why?
-Seriously.

1013
00:57:49,675 --> 00:57:51,218
I hate this.

1014
00:57:51,301 --> 00:57:53,553
-Babe.
-Hi, honey.

1015
00:57:53,637 --> 00:57:55,180
-I…
-I'm sorry, but…

1016
00:57:55,263 --> 00:57:57,724
Why is everybody apologizing?

1017
00:58:04,231 --> 00:58:05,107
Okay.

1018
00:58:06,024 --> 00:58:07,859
Hello. Table for four, please.

1019
00:58:08,777 --> 00:58:10,278
-Drinks?
-One soju and two beers.

1020
00:58:10,362 --> 00:58:12,990
Will you order the meat
after the rest of your party arrives?

1021
00:58:13,073 --> 00:58:14,658
No, they'll be here any minute.

1022
00:58:14,741 --> 00:58:16,535
Four pork belly and two pork neck.

1023
00:58:16,618 --> 00:58:18,453
-Okay.
-Please be quick.

1024
00:58:19,287 --> 00:58:21,164
I'm starving.

1025
00:58:32,759 --> 00:58:33,969
So sweet.

1026
00:58:34,678 --> 00:58:37,264
The soju sure tastes sweet tonight.

1027
00:58:40,892 --> 00:58:42,644
You've got mail.

1028
00:58:58,201 --> 00:58:59,453
Good work today, sir.

1029
00:58:59,536 --> 00:59:01,246
-Good work today, sir.
-Good work today, sir.

1030
00:59:01,329 --> 00:59:03,957
-Hi. Good job today. Sit down.
-Ma'am! One soju and a beer!

1031
00:59:04,041 --> 00:59:07,335
We happened to be hungry
right when you called to invite us to eat.

1032
00:59:07,419 --> 00:59:08,420
We were so excited.

1033
00:59:14,468 --> 00:59:16,178
Let's go for a single today.

1034
00:59:16,261 --> 00:59:17,596
I'm still hungover.

1035
00:59:18,221 --> 00:59:20,182
Still? We all drank together.

1036
00:59:21,016 --> 00:59:22,726
Someone got a hole-in-one.

1037
00:59:22,809 --> 00:59:23,935
You're right.

1038
00:59:24,019 --> 00:59:25,687
