1039
00:59:25,771 --> 00:59:27,064
The guy in the middle got it?

1040
00:59:27,147 --> 00:59:28,398
CONGRATULATIONS
HOLE-IN-ONE

1041
00:59:28,482 --> 00:59:29,691
Looks like it.

1042
00:59:30,358 --> 00:59:31,234
Wait.

1043
00:59:32,569 --> 00:59:34,237
That's Choi Sang-pil, isn't it?

1044
00:59:34,321 --> 00:59:35,739
You're right.

1045
00:59:35,822 --> 00:59:37,491
Choi Sang-pil of LK Telecom!

1046
00:59:37,574 --> 00:59:39,493
That one is the managing director of ACT.

1047
00:59:39,576 --> 00:59:41,953
They're the sales directors
from the three major telecoms.

1048
00:59:42,037 --> 00:59:43,371
You're right.

1049
00:59:43,455 --> 00:59:45,582
Why would those pricks all gather here?

1050
00:59:45,665 --> 00:59:47,667
Come on. Let's just go.

1051
00:59:47,751 --> 00:59:50,295
-Let's go.
-Hang on a minute.

1052
00:59:56,051 --> 00:59:57,219
Mr. Choi Sang-pil.

1053
00:59:57,761 --> 01:00:00,806
It's been a while. What's with your tone?

1054
01:00:00,889 --> 01:00:02,349
I'm hurt.

1055
01:00:03,183 --> 01:00:04,726
It's not like we're cops.

1056
01:00:06,019 --> 01:00:08,730
Me? I'm at Suwon Country Club.

1057
01:00:09,981 --> 01:00:12,359
I just saw your photo.

1058
01:00:12,442 --> 01:00:13,485
KIM NAK-SU

1059
01:00:13,568 --> 01:00:15,153
Korea Fair Trade Commission?

1060
01:00:15,237 --> 01:00:17,405
I guess he happened to see

1061
01:00:17,489 --> 01:00:19,324
that hole-in-one photo from back then.

1062
01:00:19,407 --> 01:00:20,367
And?

1063
01:00:20,450 --> 01:00:22,828
He just made some small talk and hung up,

1064
01:00:22,911 --> 01:00:24,329
but I know that bastard.

1065
01:00:24,412 --> 01:00:26,456
He's not the type
to call without a reason.

1066
01:00:29,042 --> 01:00:32,295
Are you saying
he caught a whiff of something?

1067
01:00:32,379 --> 01:00:35,465
One hundred percent.
He's a total Fair Trade Commission whiz.

1068
01:00:35,549 --> 01:00:37,759
I was just on the phone
with Mr. Yoon from TU.

1069
01:00:37,843 --> 01:00:39,928
We should lay low for the time being.

1070
01:00:40,011 --> 01:00:42,430
We don't want
to be suspected of colluding.

1071
01:00:42,514 --> 01:00:44,432
They're like Dobermans.

1072
01:00:44,516 --> 01:00:46,351
Once they bite, they never let go.

1073
01:00:46,434 --> 01:00:48,311
Okay. I understand.

1074
01:00:48,395 --> 01:00:50,272
I can't believe that hole-in-one

1075
01:00:50,355 --> 01:00:52,440
is coming back to bite us like this.

1076
01:00:54,234 --> 01:00:56,820
-I'm sorry.
-Let's be careful for now.

1077
01:01:31,438 --> 01:01:34,316
Fine dust hit 185 micrograms
in Daegwallyeong, Gangwon Province,

1078
01:01:34,399 --> 01:01:36,276
and 209 in Gunsan, North Jeolla Province.

1079
01:01:41,198 --> 01:01:44,284
I've done my part.

1080
01:01:45,202 --> 01:01:48,330
Seoul, Gyeonggi, Gangwon,
as well as Chungcheong and Jeolla…

1081
01:01:57,881 --> 01:02:00,467
ASAN FACTORY SAFETY MANAGEMENT
TEAM LEADER RECRUITMENT NOTICE

1082
01:02:00,592 --> 01:02:03,345
POSITION: GENERAL MANAGER OR ABOVE
20+ YEARS EXPERIENCE PREFERRED

1083
01:02:05,263 --> 01:02:06,514
IF THERE ARE NO APPLICANTS

1084
01:02:06,598 --> 01:02:08,475
MANDATORY ASSIGNMENT MAY BE ISSUED

1085
01:02:08,558 --> 01:02:10,477
I'm going to Ulleungdo Island.

1086
01:02:10,560 --> 01:02:12,479
They told me to go manage the facilities.

1087
01:02:12,562 --> 01:02:15,815
-Show us what you got.
-You really are running out of time.

1088
01:02:15,899 --> 01:02:18,944
Those bastards never planned on sending me
to Ulleungdo in the first place.

1089
01:02:19,027 --> 01:02:20,320
You have to change.

1090
01:02:20,403 --> 01:02:21,905
-They want me to quit on my own.
-Nak-su!

1091
01:02:21,992 --> 01:02:23,865
If we get an administrative sanction…

1092
01:02:23,949 --> 01:02:27,035
-We'll easily lose tens of billions.
-The company won't handle it for you.

1093
01:02:27,118 --> 01:02:28,286
They won't wait for you!

1094
01:02:28,370 --> 01:02:30,713
Living a long life
would be a disaster for me.

1095
01:02:30,789 --> 01:02:32,538
Just say sorry and be done with it.

1096
01:02:32,630 --> 01:02:34,550
Why is your team falling
so far behind Do Jin-woo's?

1097
01:02:34,626 --> 01:02:37,963
-…I'd make him managing director.
-I don't think we can solve this that way.

1098
01:02:38,046 --> 01:02:39,505
You must have thought about it too.

1099
01:02:39,631 --> 01:02:41,967
Why weren't you answering, Mr. Kim?
Please take care of…

1100
01:02:42,050 --> 01:02:43,677
-Have a great life!
-…enter this room…

1101
01:02:43,760 --> 01:02:45,470
-What's so great, Dad?
-…ashamed as a mother.

1102
01:02:45,553 --> 01:02:46,868
You have to take responsibility…

1103
01:02:47,018 --> 01:02:50,475
-…lose my chance at becoming an executive?
-…for all the choices you made.

1104
01:02:50,558 --> 01:02:53,687
We decided to send him to Asan.

1105
01:02:56,356 --> 01:02:57,941
I'm the one who made the call.

1106
01:03:01,444 --> 01:03:03,863
MR. BAEK JEONG-TAE

1107
01:03:20,505 --> 01:03:22,424
MISSED CALL
MR. BAEK JEONG-TAE

1108
01:03:22,757 --> 01:03:23,633
MR. BAEK JEONG-TAE

1109
01:03:39,524 --> 01:03:40,567
FINE DUST LEVEL
VERY HIGH

1110
01:04:19,898 --> 01:04:24,778
THE DREAM LIFE OF MR. KIM

1111
01:04:54,974 --> 01:04:57,852
You know better than anyone
how hard I've worked at ACT

1112
01:04:57,936 --> 01:04:59,270
for the past 25 years.

1113
01:04:59,354 --> 01:05:01,189
I'm still useful to the company.

1114
01:05:02,190 --> 01:05:04,526
Executives are always
on the company's side.

1115
01:05:04,609 --> 01:05:06,986
You're not in a gang.
It's not about loyalty and betrayal.

1116
01:05:07,070 --> 01:05:09,129
Let's go make some sales.
Let's get out there.

1117
01:05:09,197 --> 01:05:11,032
It's been a while, hasn't it?

1118
01:05:11,116 --> 01:05:14,160
I'll shatter it.
Like a bird breaking out from its shell,

1119
01:05:14,244 --> 01:05:15,870
I'll break your company's shell

1120
01:05:15,954 --> 01:05:18,123
so that you guys can fly.

1121
01:05:19,332 --> 01:05:20,291
Is Nak-su

1122
01:05:21,000 --> 01:05:22,460
out of the office again?

1123
01:05:23,753 --> 01:05:26,339
Isn't Nak-su going to be an executive now?

1124
01:05:27,549 --> 01:05:30,677
I guess having experience
really does make a difference.

1125
01:05:30,760 --> 01:05:31,886
Help me out, guys.

1126
01:05:32,429 --> 01:05:33,304
If you do,

1127
01:05:33,805 --> 01:05:36,391
I promise to give you
great performance reviews.

1128
01:05:41,855 --> 01:05:43,857
Subtitle translation by Yuri Kang
